  "prompt": "What are some ways you can get into Johns Hopkins University?",
  "response": "Getting into Johns Hopkins University (JHU) can be highly competitive, but there are several ways to strengthen your application and improve your chances of admission:\n\n1. **Strong Academic Record**: JHU values academic excellence, so having a strong GPA (typically 3.8 or higher) in challenging courses (AP, IB, honors) is important.\n\n2. **Standardized Test Scores**: While JHU is test-optional as of recent years, high SAT (over 1450) or ACT (over 32) scores can bolster your application.\n\n3. **Extracurricular Activities**: Demonstrating involvement and leadership in extracurricular activities can highlight your interests, passions, and dedication. This includes clubs, sports, volunteer work, and internships.\n\n4. **Letters of Recommendation**: Strong letters of recommendation from teachers, counselors, or mentors who know you well can provide valuable insights into your character and abilities.\n\n5. **Personal Statement/Essays**: Writing compelling and well-crafted essays that reflect your personality, experiences, and aspirations are critical. Make sure to articulate why you are interested in JHU and how you would contribute to the campus community.\n\n6. **Special Programs**: Consider applying for special programs or departments that may have their own set of criteria. This could include scholarships, honors programs, or specific research initiatives.\n\n7. **Demonstrated Interest**: Show genuine interest in JHU by visiting the campus (if possible), attending informational sessions, and engaging with admissions representatives. This demonstrates your enthusiasm and commitment to the school.\n\n8. **Unique Talents and Experiences**: Highlight any unique talents, experiences, or perspectives that set you apart. This could be artistic abilities, athletic achievements, entrepreneurial ventures, or significant personal challenges you've overcome.\n\n9. **Early Decision**: Applying through Early Decision can show your strong commitment to JHU and may improve your chances of admission. Be aware that this is a binding agreement.\n\n10. **Networking**: Reach out to current students, alumni, faculty, or other connections to gain insights into the application process and the culture at JHU.\n\nRemember, each applicant is unique, and showcasing your authenticity and fit for Johns Hopkins University is key to a successful application.",
